# Mos CLI-First Rule

All `.mos/` artifact operations MUST go through the `mos` CLI. Never edit `.mos` files via StrReplace, Write, sed, or any direct file manipulation.

## 5-Blade Architecture

Mos is decomposed into five subsystem binaries, each also accessible as `mos <subsystem>`:

| Blade | Binary | `mos` subcommand | Scope |
|---|---|---|---|
| **gov** | `mgov` | `mos gov` | Authoring & lifecycle — artifact CRUD, field manipulation, formatting, project setup |
| **vcs** | `mvcs` | `mos vcs` | Versioning & transport — Git-masquerading VCS for `refs/mos/*` |
| **gate** | `mgate` | `mos gate` | Verification & enforcement — quality gates, linting, CI pipeline |
| **trace** | `mtrace` | `mos trace` | Traceability across the full SE stack — needs, specs, architecture, implementation |
| **store** | `mstore` | `mos store` | Plumbing — low-level object store internals |

`mos` itself is a pure router. No commands live directly on it (except `lsp` and `completion`).

## Commands Reference

### gov (mgov) — Governance Authoring

| Operation | Command |
|---|---|
| Create artifact | `mgov <kind> create --title "..." [--kind bug] [--goal "..."] [--sprint ID] [--justifies ID]` |
| Read field | `mgov get <ID> <dot.path>` |
| Write field | `mgov set <ID> <dot.path> <value>` |
| Append to list | `mgov append <ID> <dot.path> <value>` |
| Show full artifact | `mgov show <ID>` |
| Update status | `mgov <kind> status <ID> <new-status>` |
| Delete artifact | `mgov <kind> delete <ID>` |
| Add section | `mgov <kind> add-section <ID> --name "..." --text "..."` |
| Add criterion | `mgov <kind> add-criterion <ID> --id C1 --description "..." --verified-by harness` |
| Add feature | `mgov <kind> add-feature <ID> --name "..."` |
| Add scenario | `mgov <kind> add-scenario <ID> --feature "..." --name "..."` |
| Remove block | `mgov <kind> remove-block <ID> --block "..."` |
| List artifacts | `mgov <kind> list` |
| Add spec include | `mgov <kind> add-spec <ID> <package-path> [...]` |
| Sprint: add contracts | `mgov sprint add-contract <sprint-id> <contract-id> [...]` |
| Sprint: remove contracts | `mgov sprint remove-contract <sprint-id> <contract-id> [...]` |
| Query (rich + filters) | `mgov query --kind <k> [--where field=value] [--verbose] [--format json]` |
| Format files | `mgov fmt [path]` |
| Project status | `mgov status` |

Where `<kind>` is one of: `contract`, `need`, `sprint`, `batch`, `spec`, `rule`, `binder`, `lexicon`, `doc`, `architecture`.

### vcs (mvcs) — Version Control

| Operation | Command |
|---|---|
| Commit | `mvcs commit -m "..."` |
| Log (oneline) | `mvcs log --oneline -n 5` |
| Log (JSON) | `mvcs log --format json -n 3` |
| Log (with stat) | `mvcs log --stat -n 1` |
| Push | `mvcs push` |
| Pull | `mvcs pull` |
| Status | `mvcs status` |
| Branch | `mvcs branch <name>` |

### gate (mgate) — Quality Gates

| Operation | Command |
|---|---|
| Lint | `mgate lint` |
| Lint (agent mode) | `mgate lint --agent` |
| Lint (summary) | `mgate lint --severity error --summary -v` |
| Validate (parse-only) | `mgate validate` |
| Audit | `mgate audit [--trend] [--velocity]` |
| Harness | `mgate harness run [--rule <id>]` |
| Doctor | `mgate doctor` |
| CI pipeline | `mgate ci [--fast] [--fix]` |
| Hook install | `mgate hook install` |

### trace (mtrace) — Traceability

| Operation | Command |
|---|---|
| Context mesh | `mtrace mesh <path> [--format text\|json\|mermaid]` |
| Architecture sync | `mtrace architecture sync [--path .] [--scanner auto] [--markdown] [--grouped]` |
| Survey | `mtrace survey <path>` |
| Clone artifacts | `mtrace clone --from <path> --kinds <k1,k2> [--state S] [--group G]` |
| Generate specs | `mgov spec generate [--state current\|desired] [--exclude dir1,dir2]` |

### store (mstore) — Plumbing

| Operation | Command |
|---|---|
| Store status | `mstore status` |
| Verify integrity | `mstore verify` |
| Audit log | `mstore log [--tail N]` |

## Specification Grouping & Candidate Status

Specifications support a `group` field (free-text, derived from top-level source directory) and a `candidate` lifecycle status:

- **`candidate`**: Generated/proposed spec, not yet reviewed. Comes before `draft` in the lifecycle.
- **`draft`**: Accepted for refinement.
- **`group`**: Subsystem tag (e.g. `builtin`, `compat`, `moslib`) for filtering and organizing large spec sets.

Use `mgov query --kind specification --where group=builtin` to filter by group. Use `mgov set <ID> status draft` to promote a candidate to draft.

## Context Mesh

Use `mtrace mesh <path>` to understand the governance context of any code package. It resolves a filesystem path or package name to linked specs, contracts, needs, sprints, and architectural import edges.

- **text** (default): tree view grouped by kind
- **json**: full graph with nodes and edges for programmatic consumption
- **mermaid**: subgraph diagram for visual review

Use this command **before** making changes to understand what governance artifacts are relevant to the code you're about to touch.

## Schema Evolution

The mos CLI is under active development. Commands, flags, and subcommands change frequently. Before assuming a flag doesn't exist or a command works a certain way, run `<binary> <command> --help` to check the current interface. Do this especially:

- At the start of a session
- Before creating or updating artifacts
- When a command fails unexpectedly (the flag may have been renamed or moved)

Do not rely on memorized flag lists from previous sessions.

## Escape Hatch

If the CLI cannot perform a required operation (missing subcommand, unsupported field, bulk edit beyond what `mgov set`/`mgov update` supports), then:

1. State clearly: "The mos CLI does not support [operation]. Editing the file directly as a workaround."
2. File a bug or feature request via: `mgov contract create --kind bug --title "CLI: missing support for [operation]"` (or `--kind feat`).
3. Only then fall back to direct file edit.
4. Run `mgov fmt` on the touched file afterward.

## Package Layout

### Layer 0 (Foundation) — no internal deps
`moslib/dsl`, `moslib/schema`, `moslib/store`, `moslib/model`, `moslib/names`

### Layer 1 (Govern Core) — depends on Layer 0 only
`moslib/artifact`, `moslib/registry`

### Layer 2 (Domain) — depends on Layer 0 + Layer 1
`moslib/linter`, `moslib/harness`, `moslib/vcs`, `moslib/guard`, `moslib/arch`, `moslib/mesh`, `moslib/clone`, `moslib/survey`, `moslib/topology`

### Layer 3 (CLI) — thin adapters
| Subsystem | CLI packages |
|---|---|
| gov | `cmd/mos/govern`, `cmd/mos/contract`, `cmd/mos/rule`, `cmd/mos/spec`, `cmd/mos/binder`, `cmd/mos/lexicon`, `cmd/mos/config`, `cmd/mos/generic` |
| vcs | `cmd/mos/vcscmd` |
| gate | `cmd/mos/gatecmd`, `cmd/mos/ci` |
| trace | `cmd/mos/tracecmd` |
| store | `cmd/mos/storecmd` |

### Wiring
`cmd/internal/wire` — shared dependency injection callbacks.
`cmd/internal/subsystem` — builder functions returning `*cobra.Command` for each subsystem.

**Golden Rule**: `artifact/` is the ONLY package that touches `.mos/` files. Everything else goes through its API.

**Cross-tool restriction**: No Layer 2 package imports another Layer 2 package from a different sub-tool.

## Examples

```bash
# Create a bug
mgov contract create --kind bug --title "Linter false positives" --goal "..."

# Set a slug
mgov set CON-2026-018 slug macro-ide-arch

# Update status to complete
mgov contract status CON-2026-171 complete

# Add a section to a need
mgov need add-section NEED-2026-001 --name "Principle" --text "..."

# Sprint contract management
mgov sprint add-contract SPR-2026-015 CON-2026-187 CON-2026-188
mgov sprint remove-contract SPR-2026-015 CON-2026-189

# Query with filters
mgov query --kind contract --where status=active --verbose
mgov query --kind contract --where status=draft --format json

# Context mesh: understand governance context of a package
mtrace mesh moslib/governance
mtrace mesh cmd/mos --format json
mtrace mesh ./moslib/linter --format mermaid

# Generate specs from architecture
mgov spec generate --state current
mgov spec generate --state current --exclude t,Documentation

# Clone specs from another project
mtrace clone --from ~/Workspace/git --kinds specification --group builtin

# Promote a candidate spec to draft
mgov set SPEC-2026-033 status draft

# VCS operations
mvcs commit -m "feat: add query filtering"
mvcs log --oneline -n 5
mvcs push

# Architecture
mtrace architecture sync
mtrace architecture sync --grouped --scanner go

# Quality gates
mgate lint --severity error --summary -v
mgate ci --fast
mgate doctor
```
